The paper focuses on the usability and security of fall-back authentication, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of human-computer interaction (cs.HC), computer security and cryptography (cs.CR), cyber security (cs.CY), social and information networks (cs.SI), and graphics (cs.GR). The use of a serious game to improve the memorability of security questions involves the use of visual cues and psychology research, which are relevant to these sub-categories. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.HC and cs.CR, followed by cs.CY, cs.SI, and cs.GR.
